-- Jeddah Desalination Unit Resumes Operations After Fire Incident
-- B y   D e e m a   A l m a s h a b i
-- 2013-06-15T08:52:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-15/jeddah-desalination-unit-resumes-operations-after-fire-incident.html
The  Jeddah  Phase 4 desalination unit
on the Red Sea coast has resumed operations after a fire erupted
on June 13, according to a  statement  today by the  Saline Water
Conversion Corp.   The fire was brought under control by firefighters and no
casualties were reported. No shortage in water supplies has been
detected and the city of Jeddah,  Saudi Arabia , is being supplied
with 1.2 million cubic meters of water daily, according to
company spokesman Abdulaziz al-Mazroa.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Deema Almashabi in Riyadh at 
 dalmashabi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
